item.title: 317-Delta | Need help Adding Custom Items/NPC's
item.dc:creator: @sk8rdude461 sk8rdude461
item.description:
@sk8rdude461 wrote:

if(X = ****) {

Is basically the same thing as:

case ****:

The difference is one is in a switch statement, and looks cleaner, and is also easier to use.

item.dc:creator: @Welliton_inc Welliton_inc
item.description:
@Welliton_inc wrote:

Are the customs you’re trying to add looking like random objects?

Probably because you’re either not adding the models, or using a model ID that is already being used (don’t or you’re going to suffer the consequences which are a pain to fix), or you’re adding the models in the wrong place.
